nodes.title: FreeU Option
widgets_values:
FreeU is an experimental set of parameters that aims to improve image quality and detail. I have it Bypassed normally, but should you wish to use it you can un-bypass it and see if the results are to your liking. More info:

https://github.com/ChenyangSi/FreeU

https://wandb.ai/nasirk24/UNET-FreeU-SDXL/reports/FreeU-SDXL-Optimal-Parameters--Vmlldzo1NDg4NTUw

Be sure to set a Controlnet that is appropriate for the type of image you are passing through via this switch! Use 1. Passthrough if you are supplying an already-prepped controlnet image (for example, if you have generated a depth map from Blender to use to guide the model, or a drawing you've already prepared like lineart or a scribble, or if you are using an Openpose model.
This Iterative Upscaler is based off of Scott Detweiler's excellent tutorial here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t3lT_04A9j0&t=1101s&ab_channel=ScottDetweiler

sometimes you want to keep the seed but generate options with dfferent settings. if you enable the switch above, it will add an unique random id prior to the seed. In this way, you can change settings but not the seed and keep assets for a specific generation grouped.

if disabled, this id will be skipped, andimages generated with same project folder/project name/seed will be overwritten each generation.

nodes.title: Important Note RE Controlnet and its connection to this section!
widgets_values: You must also disable the controlnet stack or if you want to generate in Txt2Img mode ONLY. IE, you can select an SDXL latent size that is different than that supplied by the controlnet processing (it use the SDXL res closest to the input image) or any arbitrary size in the custom, but it will attempt to use the controlnet if that switch is stlll set to "on."
